# Running selene and luacheck

Both linter configs live under `nvim/` (`nvim/selene.toml` + its std
`nvim/vim.toml`, and `nvim/.luacheckrc`) — not at the repo root.

## selene — run from `nvim/`

selene reads `selene.toml` from the **current directory only** (no parent or
file-relative search). Running it from elsewhere produces dozens of bogus
`error[undefined_variable]: 'vim' is not defined` errors because it can't load
the `vim` std. Always `cd nvim` first:

```bash
cd nvim && selene .config/nvim/lua/user/wezterm.lua
```

## luacheck — works from anywhere

luacheck resolves `.luacheckrc` relative to each checked file (walking up from
the file's directory), so `nvim/.luacheckrc` is found no matter the cwd. No
special handling needed:

```bash
luacheck nvim/.config/nvim/lua/user/wezterm.lua
```
